1
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:20,480
(Kim Da Mi)

2
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:23,390
(Shin Ye Eun)

3
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,760
(Heo Nam Jun)

4
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,530
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

5
00:00:37,940 --> 00:00:41,970
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

6
00:00:43,270 --> 00:00:45,810
(Written by Yang Hee Seung and Kim Bo Ram)

7
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:50,850
(Directed by Kim Sang Ho)

8
00:00:52,050 --> 00:00:53,050
All clear!

9
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:59,060
(A Hundred Memories)

10
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:07,366
(Cheongah Bus)

11
00:01:07,390 --> 00:01:08,690
Manager.

12
00:01:08,890 --> 00:01:10,900
Please, you have to help me out this time.

13
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:14,070
I'm begging you, please?

14
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:17,770
My mom just had surgery.

15
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:20,016
If you can just adjust
this one dispatch for me,

16
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,960
I'll work straight through
without any days off.

17
00:01:22,670 --> 00:01:24,156
I'll handle all the fare deposits, too.

18
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:25,386
You know I'm good with mental math...

19
00:01:25,410 --> 00:01:27,210
Forget it!

20
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,286
I don't need you to
handle the fare deposits.

21
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:32,420
We already don't have enough conductors.

22
00:01:33,050 --> 00:01:34,396
Manager, just this once...

23
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:36,536
Manager, my foot. I told
you, the answer is no!

24
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,736
Think about it.

25
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:39,666
If I made an exception for every sob story,

26
00:01:39,690 --> 00:01:41,990
how could I possibly run this company?

27
00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:45,836
If you want to leave a hole
so bad, why don't you just quit?

28
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:47,230
Just make a clean break of it.

29
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:51,740
The only hole I see
is the one in your sock.

30
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:54,346
So who mends that holey
sock of yours for you?

31
00:01:54,370 --> 00:01:56,386
Your poor old mother has to, right?

32
00:01:56,410 --> 00:01:58,256
Since you still haven't
managed to get married.

33
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:00,126
If you're not going to mend
it, then keep your mouth shut.

34
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,526
And it's a mother just like her

35
00:02:01,550 --> 00:02:04,180
who had to be cut open
and stitched back up.

36
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:06,296
And you're just brushing
her daughter off like that?

37
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,020
That's just heartless!

38
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:10,966
We'll cover for Yeong Rye.

39
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:12,070
So that should work, right?

40
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,660
Guys...

41
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:19,200
Look at you all, putting
on this little show?

42
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:23,770
What an impressive display of friendship!

43
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:25,940
But too bad.

44
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,440
You girls alone aren't enough to cover it.

45
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:34,180
So, am I going to approve this or am I not?

46
00:02:34,810 --> 00:02:38,120
Ms. Koh! Do I approve it, or do I not?

47
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:41,090
Then I'll cover the shift, too.

48
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:48,090
With three of us covering,
we should be able to manage.

49
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,400
Jong Hee.

50
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:01,470
Aren't you all pushing
yourselves too hard for me?

51
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:05,440
It'll be exhausting working
without any days off.

52
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,780
Hey, now.

53
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:08,280
What are friends for?

54
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,480
Now, you're starting to hurt my feelings.

55
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,680
That's right.

56
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:14,490
To be blunt,

57
00:03:14,690 --> 00:03:16,120
if we were in your shoes,

58
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:19,020
you'd do the same for us, wouldn't you?

59
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:20,906
Exactly.

60
00:03:20,930 --> 00:03:23,600
That's what friends are for. Right?

61
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:31,170
But how long are those
two going to keep this up?

62
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:33,090
It's making us uncomfortable just watching.

63
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:40,550
All because of one stupid player.

64
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:44,050
A friendship flimsier than
tissue is torn to shreds.

65
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:46,350
Tell me about it.

66
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:50,220
They used to be inseparable,
for goodness' sake.

67
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:52,490
I don't get it either.

68
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:56,360
There are plenty of fish in the
sea. Why act like this over a guy?

69
00:04:18,150 --> 00:04:19,220
Here.

70
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:24,560
Could you give this to Seo Jong Hee for me?

71
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:40,446
(Episode 4: One Step Behind)

72
00:04:40,470 --> 00:04:44,756
(Episode 4: One Step Behind)

73
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:46,726
(Jeongsin High School)

74
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:50,456
Loser, moron, airhead, simpleton.

75
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:53,796
- Loser, moron, idiot.
- Is that all you've got?

76
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:54,850
Hit it harder.

77
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,420
Idiot!

78
00:04:58,390 --> 00:04:59,390
Hey.

79
00:04:59,930 --> 00:05:01,706
You know, if I had a time machine?

80
00:05:01,730 --> 00:05:04,000
I'd go straight back
to the exhibition match.

81
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,006
Then I'd cut Deok Gu off at the pass,

82
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:07,800
and knock him out with an uppercut.

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,760
Then Yeong Rye would be like,

84
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,546
"Oh, my. Sang Cheol."

85
00:05:11,570 --> 00:05:13,440
"How can you be so manly and amazing?"

86
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,640
"I think I've fallen head
over heels for you."

87
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:16,900
That's what she'd say, right?

88
00:05:20,910 --> 00:05:22,010
You lunatic.

89
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:25,120
Right? I'm a lunatic, like you said.

90
00:05:28,590 --> 00:05:30,920
What is wrong with me?

91
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,330
Now that I know it's too late,

92
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,530
I find myself missing her even more.

93
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:40,770
If it's that bad, why don't
you visit her in the hospital?

94
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,130
Visit her at the hospital?

95
00:05:42,630 --> 00:05:43,700
Who?

96
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:53,880
For goodness' sake, what's all the fuss?

97
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,650
I said, just go already.

98
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:59,420
Good grief. You're so stubborn.

99
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:01,420
You're as stubborn as a mule.

100
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:03,120
I'm telling you, I'm fine.

101
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:06,630
My coworkers said they'd
cover my shifts, I told you.

102
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:09,490
In that case,

103
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,060
you should visit our home.

104
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:14,170
Check on the kids,

105
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:17,970
do the laundry, and make
some side dishes, okay?

106
00:06:18,370 --> 00:06:20,770
Yeong Sik can't handle all that by himself.

107
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:24,060
With all his studies and tutoring,
he's already struggling as it is.

108
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:25,186
Goodness.

109
00:06:25,210 --> 00:06:26,210
Mom.

110
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:29,126
Even in a time like this, all
you care about is Yeong Sik?

111
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:31,150
Of course. He's the pillar of this family.

112
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,820
Then what does that make me?

113
00:06:34,020 --> 00:06:35,150
You're...

114
00:06:36,890 --> 00:06:38,760
You're my daughter. My eldest daughter.

115
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:42,830
Right.

116
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:44,960
I'm the eldest daughter.

117
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:48,830
The one who has to earn money
and take care of her siblings.

118
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:51,646
When my own mother
treats me so thoughtlessly,

119
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:54,016
who in the world would
ever cherish me? Right?

120
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,610
Good grief, this girl.

121
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,380
Did you wake up on the
wrong side of the bed?

122
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:01,180
Why are you being so prickly?

123
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,280
I don't know.

124
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:05,950
That's just how the words
are coming out today.

125
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,966
Look who's here, the pillar of the family.

126
00:07:10,990 --> 00:07:14,060
I'm going to go look after the kids,
do laundry, and make some food.

127
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,930
So you, Mr. Pillar, can take care of Mom.

128
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:18,770
And don't just wolf down the
canned peaches by yourself.

129
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:20,090
Make sure Mom gets some, too.

130
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,540
- What's going on with her?
- I don't know.

131
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:27,910
Maybe something happened at work?

132
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:29,786
Stomp.

133
00:07:29,810 --> 00:07:33,350
- Get clean.
- Get clean.

134
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:35,786
- Jong Hee. I'm good at this, right?
- Yes? You're the best.

135
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:37,126
- Me too, right?
- The best!

136
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:38,850
- Harder! Stomp.
- Jong Hee.

137
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:41,126
- Yeong Rye!
- Yeong Rye!

138
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:42,150
You're here?

139
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:45,290
What are you doing here without telling me?

140
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,630
When did you get here?

141
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:48,790
A little while ago.

142
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,560
Over there.

143
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,650
I know you couldn't
make it to class yesterday.

144
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:58,240
You know I don't
normally take notes, right?

145
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,680
But I took really detailed notes
with the fountain pen you gave me.

146
00:08:02,470 --> 00:08:05,840
And don't get on my case if it
looks like a bunch of chicken scratch.

147
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,850
I really did my best.

148
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,220
Stomp!

149
00:08:14,890 --> 00:08:17,796
What are you waiting for?
We need to feed the kids, right?

150
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:20,506
They've been working really
hard, so I bet they're starving.

151
00:08:20,530 --> 00:08:22,366
- Yes.
- Right? You're hungry, aren't you?

152
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:23,500
- Yes!
- Yes!

153
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:25,230
All right.

154
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,060
I'll go make some food right away.

155
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,890
I love the flowerbed at your house.

156
00:08:54,530 --> 00:08:55,790
The flowers are so pretty,

157
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,500
and your vegetable garden is great, too.

158
00:09:06,570 --> 00:09:09,410
Your mother's doing okay now, right?

159
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,040
Yes.

160
00:09:11,580 --> 00:09:12,680
But.

161
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:16,580
I won't let her leave the
hospital until she's fully recovered.

162
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:19,756
I'm worried she'll try
to go right back to work.

163
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:23,220
Yes, that sounds exactly like your mom.

164
00:09:23,890 --> 00:09:26,420
I was so shocked when I
heard she was going into surgery.

165
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:27,960
I nearly fainted.

166
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,206
That can't ever happen again.

167
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:31,230
Yes.

168
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:33,900
Here.

169
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,186
Jong Hee.

170
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,280
Yes?

171
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:57,290
Here.

172
00:09:58,820 --> 00:09:59,820
What is it?

173
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,130
On the day my mom collapsed,

174
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:09,570
I ran into Han Jae Pil on the street.

175
00:10:09,770 --> 00:10:10,870
Han Jae Pil?

176
00:10:12,370 --> 00:10:14,110
(Han Jae Pil)

177
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:17,980
I was desperately trying to catch a cab,

178
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,610
and he gave me a ride to the hospital

179
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:22,426
in his family's car.

180
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:23,550
Really?

181
00:10:24,180 --> 00:10:25,480
That was really nice of him.

182
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:31,960
He

183
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,590
Asked me to give this to you.

184
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:36,090
- Me?
- Yes.

185
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,230
You know how he invited
us to the boxing gym?

186
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:44,400
I guess he did that for you.

187
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:46,810
And I had no idea.

188
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:50,140
I totally jumped the gun
and got my hopes up.

189
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,680
Really?

190
00:10:53,650 --> 00:10:54,850
What a strange guy.

191
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,520
I don't know about that.

192
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:03,190
But anyway, I gave it to you.

193
00:11:04,060 --> 00:11:05,320
Mission accomplished!

194
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:07,860
What about you?

195
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,660
I thought you were into him.

196
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,400
Me?

197
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:17,446
No, I thought he was
the one who was into me.

198
00:11:17,470 --> 00:11:20,286
So I decided to give him a chance.

199
00:11:20,310 --> 00:11:21,316
You know, something like that.

200
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:23,010
No, I'm not.

201
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:25,280
He's not even my type.

202
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:27,910
Really?

203
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,640
Why?

204
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:55,410
You don't like him?

205
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:57,540
It's not about liking him or not.

206
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,350
I'm not interested in dating.

207
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,770
I don't have the energy for it either.

208
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,520
Besides,

209
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:11,260
he knows nothing about me.

210
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,600
I'm going to get more snacks.

211
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,860
You want some too, right?

212
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,026
Wait. Really?

213
00:12:35,050 --> 00:12:36,890
You just ran into her
on the street by chance?

214
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,820
Yes.

215
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:40,950
That should've been me!

216
00:12:41,490 --> 00:12:43,970
I should've given you a ride,
even if I had to borrow a truck.

217
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:46,630
Maybe I should visit her in the hospital.

218
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,790
Go ahead.

219
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:49,936
I don't know if she'll be
happy to see you, though.

220
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,530
Hey, come with me!

221
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,680
You're the one with an excuse
to go, since you gave her a ride.

222
00:12:55,170 --> 00:12:56,600
I may have an excuse,

223
00:12:57,570 --> 00:12:59,870
but no desire to go. Why should...

224
00:13:01,610 --> 00:13:02,746
"Why should..."

225
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:03,840
What?

226
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:09,810
Let's go.

227
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:12,280
Let's go. I'll come with you.

228
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,090
Really?

229
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:15,890
Gosh. I'm so excited.

230
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,890
Should I get something
like flowers or fruit?

231
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,260
I'm getting the hiccups. Look.

232
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,400
Hi.

233
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,070
Hey.

234
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:31,040
Hi.

235
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:39,210
Well, I heard from Jae Pil and...

236
00:13:39,410 --> 00:13:42,026
If I hadn't heard, that's one thing,
but I can't pretend I don't know.

237
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:44,020
It just didn't feel right, as a friend.

238
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:47,466
I mean, we're not exactly friends,
but we're not exactly strangers.

239
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:49,850
It's a really hard relationship to define.

240
00:13:51,490 --> 00:13:53,466
What? Did you say something, Jae Pil?

241
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:56,206
He said you must be
sick of the hospital food.

242
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:57,276
- Right.
- Yes.

243
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:00,230
You see, Sang Cheol's
parents run a stall at the market.

244
00:14:00,330 --> 00:14:01,806
Right.

245
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:03,606
A little something in the food business.

246
00:14:03,630 --> 00:14:05,600
It's a pretty big operation
for a market stall.

247
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,940
They sell pickled vegetables
and fermented seafood.

248
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:09,500
And business is surprisingly good.

249
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:11,156
Not to brag,

250
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:13,640
but everyone around
here says it's the real deal.

251
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:16,810
Everyone loves their food, right?

252
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,890
Right. This is for you.

253
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:24,636
Thank you.

254
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:26,820
- Yes.
- I'll enjoy it.

255
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,906
How's your mom doing?
Is she feeling a lot better?

256
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:36,630
She is, thanks to you.

257
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:40,300
Actually, she was just asking
who the friend was that drove her.

258
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:41,646
She said to tell you thank you.

259
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:43,110
It was nothing.

260
00:14:43,210 --> 00:14:44,680
Of course. I was happy to do it.

261
00:14:49,350 --> 00:14:50,350
Hey.

262
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,820
Can we have a moment?

263
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:00,060
What?

264
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:16,670
Well...

265
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:18,810
Yes?

266
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,480
About that note from the other day...

267
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:25,080
Oh, right.

268
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:29,420
It got to her, right?

269
00:15:29,950 --> 00:15:30,960
What'd she say?

270
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:32,560
Well...

271
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,130
Jong Hee's not really

272
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:39,060
in a place to be seeing anyone right now.

273
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,970
Oh, is that right?

274
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:44,940
Then why did she even
come on the group date?

275
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:47,740
Was she just there for fun?

276
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,510
I mean, that can happen.

277
00:15:50,910 --> 00:15:52,210
That can happen, sure.

278
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:54,886
Sorry for making things awkward for you.

279
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:57,620
I feel bad bothering her
now, with her sick mom.

280
00:15:57,820 --> 00:16:00,590
No, don't worry. It's fine, really.

281
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:06,836
(Wonhwa Jaeil Hospital)

282
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:09,106
Gosh. So much for acting
uninterested in the group date.

283
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:10,506
You were so stoic, playing hard to get.

284
00:16:10,530 --> 00:16:11,560
Knock it off.

285
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:14,570
When did that all happen, you sly cat.

286
00:16:15,170 --> 00:16:17,270
I said knock it off. Say one more word.

287
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,510
Come on. When did you fall for her?

288
00:16:20,710 --> 00:16:23,240
Was it at the roller rink? When
Jong Hee took her jacket off?

289
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,920
Or was it when she was
trying to hold you back?

290
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:29,150
Don't tell me it was love at first sight.

291
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,896
You wouldn't let it go when I
was crushing on Yeong Rye.

292
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,026
And here you are, up all
night thinking about Jong Hee.

293
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:36,496
So that's what's been going on!

294
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:37,966
All right! I'll stop!

295
00:16:37,990 --> 00:16:39,266
- Didn't I say knock it off?
- I said I'll stop!

296
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,306
Jae Pil! I'll stop!

297
00:16:41,330 --> 00:16:43,006
I'll stop, all right?

298
00:16:43,030 --> 00:16:44,276
What's gotten into you?

299
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:45,500
Jae Pil.

300
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,146
Tell me whatever you want to eat.

301
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:49,700
To celebrate you getting shot
down, I'll pay for everything.

302
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:52,816
I'm paying, I said. What's wrong?

303
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,170
I said I'm treating!

304
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:49,430
When did you get here?

305
00:17:49,530 --> 00:17:51,776
You must not be a light sleeper.
You can just fall asleep anywhere.

306
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:53,000
I am a light sleeper.

307
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,520
I often sleep in places like
this. I've gotten used to it.

308
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,100
Kids, your brother is here.

309
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,840
What? Yeong Sik.

310
00:18:01,410 --> 00:18:02,710
Yeong Sik.

311
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:04,186
Did you two have fun and play nicely?

312
00:18:04,210 --> 00:18:05,210
- Yes.
- Yes.

313
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,410
Yeong Sik. Look at this.

314
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:11,350
Jong Hee drew this for me.
She did a great job, right?

315
00:18:11,620 --> 00:18:14,366
Gosh. She's not much of an artist, is she?

316
00:18:14,390 --> 00:18:15,550
Agreed.

317
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:17,490
You don't have to be good at everything.

318
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:20,090
Let's go play inside.

319
00:18:23,330 --> 00:18:25,130
You haven't eaten yet, right?

320
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,806
Yeong Rye made kimchi stew and side dishes.

321
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,546
- Do you want me to serve you some?
- No, it's all right. You should go.

322
00:18:29,570 --> 00:18:30,576
You need to get some rest, too.

323
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,076
It's tough when you
don't rest on your day off.

324
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,860
I thought you had tutoring later.
Are you leaving the kids all alone?

325
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:37,710
Yeong Mi said it gets
even scarier at night.

326
00:18:37,910 --> 00:18:38,910
I'll figure it out.

327
00:18:41,610 --> 00:18:43,210
- Thanks for everything.
- Gosh.

328
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:46,330
I'm just trying to do a good
deed, so why do I feel kicked out?

329
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,350
You just smiled.

330
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,260
So you do know how to smile.

331
00:18:54,690 --> 00:18:56,810
I was starting to think
you were allergic to smiling.

332
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,330
Aren't you leaving?

333
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,830
- I'm going.
- Okay.

334
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:08,846
- This is totally my style.
- Oh, that's pretty.

335
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:09,916
Hey, look at this.

336
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:12,116
- This is prettier.
- I know, right?

337
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:14,480
- But I think this suits you better.
- Really?

338
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:16,210
This one.

339
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,900
This is no fun by myself.

340
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,800
I miss Koh Yeong Rye.

341
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:50,110
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

342
00:19:51,250 --> 00:19:52,250
Hey.

343
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,020
Isn't that her?

344
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,790
Seo Jong Hee?

345
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:02,006
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

346
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:03,990
(Jungang Supermarket)

347
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,760
When did he get here?

348
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:11,740
- Yeong Sik!
- Is it good?

349
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:15,110
All right, let's go over this again.

350
00:20:15,340 --> 00:20:18,180
Until I'm back from my tutoring,
what are you supposed to do?

351
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:20,010
We wait here quietly.

352
00:20:20,210 --> 00:20:22,080
And we don't move a single step.

353
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,380
That's right.

354
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:25,750
- Yeong Bae, take good care of her.
- Okay.

355
00:20:25,850 --> 00:20:28,690
And if you need the bathroom,
tell the lady at the market.

356
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,590
- I've already spoken to her.
- Okay.

357
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,566
When I'm done later, I'll come back
and buy you an even better treat.

358
00:20:33,590 --> 00:20:35,860
An even better treat? Like jjajangmyeon?

359
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:37,360
That sounds delicious.

360
00:20:41,030 --> 00:20:43,100
- Oh, Mr. Koh.
- Hello.

361
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,740
And who are these two?

362
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:48,910
Your siblings?

363
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:51,280
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

364
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:54,080
But why are your siblings here?

365
00:20:55,810 --> 00:20:58,056
Oh, my. Don't tell me you're
making them wait out here?

366
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,396
Yes, my mother's in the hospital,
so I didn't really have a choice.

367
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:02,420
I see.

368
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:05,536
Oh, dear. You really
shouldn't. In this day and age,

369
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,466
leaving the kids out
here all by themselves...

370
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:09,736
They look like they're my Sae Ri's age.

371
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:12,130
And she looks even younger than her.

372
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:36,720
Stop it.

373
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:39,160
What's wrong?

374
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,060
Goodness.

375
00:21:43,430 --> 00:21:45,700
You two haven't eaten dinner, right?

376
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:52,470
Here you go.

377
00:21:52,970 --> 00:21:55,010
I hope you like omelette rice.

378
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:57,086
It's one of my Sae Ri's favourites to eat.

379
00:21:57,110 --> 00:21:58,316
Do you like it?

380
00:21:58,340 --> 00:22:00,956
- I do.
- Good. I'm glad.

381
00:22:00,980 --> 00:22:02,680
Go on, eat up.

382
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:03,880
Dig in.

383
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:54,060
Her name is Ju Ju.

384
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:57,900
My dad brought her back for
me from a business trip to Paris.

385
00:22:58,100 --> 00:22:59,740
I'm the one who named her Ju Ju.

386
00:23:00,570 --> 00:23:02,840
She's five years old.

387
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:12,420
This is from my dad's
business trip to Finland.

388
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:16,566
That's where Santa Claus
and Rudolph live, you know?

389
00:23:16,590 --> 00:23:18,320
Oh, yes.

390
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:29,800
Here.

391
00:23:31,940 --> 00:23:33,140
Gosh.

392
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,410
It's called a music box.

393
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:38,980
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

394
00:23:39,380 --> 00:23:40,580
Then it's yours.

395
00:23:40,780 --> 00:23:41,950
It's my gift to you.

396
00:23:42,150 --> 00:23:43,610
- Really?
- Yes!

397
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:48,620
She told her she could have it.

398
00:23:50,290 --> 00:23:54,590
I would hide a single rainbow
candy so Yeong Mi wouldn't ask for it.

399
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,860
With a beautiful smile,
just like a princess,

400
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:01,670
she told her she could
have this expensive gift.

401
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,880
Finish these by our next session.

402
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,180
And mark the ones you get stuck on.

403
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:20,650
Okay.

404
00:24:21,090 --> 00:24:23,296
Don't just mark them without trying first.

405
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:24,560
I can always tell.

406
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:26,660
Sure.

407
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,160
Yes, sir.

408
00:24:29,860 --> 00:24:32,230
Is something wrong? You seem so out of it.

409
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,560
You couldn't focus the whole time, too.

410
00:24:34,970 --> 00:24:36,970
When have I ever been motivated

411
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:38,300
to study?

412
00:24:43,270 --> 00:24:44,380
Mr. Koh.

413
00:24:45,010 --> 00:24:46,640
Have you ever been shot down before?

414
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:52,550
If shot down means
confessing and getting rejected,

415
00:24:53,620 --> 00:24:55,550
then no, not even once.

416
00:24:56,150 --> 00:24:58,390
You know you sound very obnoxious, right?

417
00:24:59,390 --> 00:25:00,560
I know.

418
00:25:04,330 --> 00:25:06,000
I mean, what is it that women

419
00:25:07,030 --> 00:25:08,976
find attractive in a guy?

420
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,946
Do you have to be smart
like you, for starters?

421
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:16,016
Like all intellectual?
And wear shirts like this?

422
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,170
Who is she?

423
00:25:21,210 --> 00:25:22,410
I'm not talking about me.

424
00:25:24,550 --> 00:25:26,026
I was just curious, that's all.

425
00:25:26,050 --> 00:25:28,326
Class is over, so you should
go. Your siblings are waiting.

426
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:29,920
And I have to get to the gym.

427
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,300
(Giant Boxing Gym)

428
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,570
Hey, Han Jae Pil!

429
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:49,040
You made it.

430
00:25:49,410 --> 00:25:51,156
Greetings, my senior.

431
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:52,510
- You made it.
- Yes.

432
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:57,830
I've got some juicy
information you're going to love.

433
00:25:57,880 --> 00:26:00,520
Guess who I saw earlier when I
was on my way to my mom's store?

434
00:26:02,050 --> 00:26:03,150
Who'd you see?

435
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:04,496
I don't know.

436
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:07,096
Should I tell you or not?

437
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:09,566
Should I tell you or not?

438
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:11,436
Don't. I don't care. Stop.

439
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:13,060
You're going to regret this. Seriously.

440
00:26:16,630 --> 00:26:18,600
I saw Seo Jong Hee earlier!

441
00:26:25,310 --> 00:26:26,380
Who's that?

442
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,286
Am I supposed to know her?
I've never heard that name before.

443
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:31,780
Is this a pride of a man or something?

444
00:26:32,950 --> 00:26:34,226
Well...

445
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:37,760
She went to Vivaldi Music Cafe,
where we had that group date.

446
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:40,920
Seeing as she was going in
alone, she must be a regular.

447
00:26:44,230 --> 00:26:47,360
You don't need to try ten times,
but you can at least try once.

448
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,600
No? Are you giving up? Just like that?

449
00:26:50,570 --> 00:26:51,670
You're giving up?

450
00:26:52,340 --> 00:26:53,416
Why is there so much
dust on this? Hold that.

451
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,470
What?

452
00:26:56,840 --> 00:26:57,840
I'm going to go change.

453
00:26:58,510 --> 00:27:00,840
Are you giving up?

454
00:27:01,250 --> 00:27:02,280
Fine.

455
00:27:05,980 --> 00:27:10,320
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

456
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:30,110
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

457
00:27:57,170 --> 00:27:58,470
Darn it.

458
00:27:59,540 --> 00:28:02,310
It held up for so long,
but it finally gave out.

459
00:28:06,910 --> 00:28:08,550
What am I going to do?

460
00:28:20,890 --> 00:28:22,030
Come on.

461
00:28:22,430 --> 00:28:24,150
What are you going to do about yours, then?

462
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,130
Me?

463
00:28:33,570 --> 00:28:35,070
I can stay like this.

464
00:28:36,470 --> 00:28:38,410
Then give that to me.

465
00:28:38,610 --> 00:28:40,756
No, I'm the one with the broken slippers.

466
00:28:40,780 --> 00:28:42,250
Just wear it.

467
00:28:42,450 --> 00:28:44,720
You came out to go to
the supermarket, right?

468
00:28:45,580 --> 00:28:47,780
I can just go back inside like this.

469
00:28:47,950 --> 00:28:50,390
No, it's fine. That would look ridiculous.

470
00:28:52,060 --> 00:28:53,590
You've got an image to maintain.

471
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:05,500
You wench.

472
00:29:06,270 --> 00:29:08,770
I'm sorry, Hae Ja.

473
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:12,580
I don't know what came over me.

474
00:29:15,150 --> 00:29:17,950
No, I'm the one who's sorry.

475
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:22,450
Your hair is already so
thin, and I went and pulled it.

476
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:26,966
Without you, I have no
one to hang out with,

477
00:29:26,990 --> 00:29:28,890
and no one to talk to.

478
00:29:30,490 --> 00:29:32,006
You can have Driver Kim.

479
00:29:32,030 --> 00:29:34,806
No, you have him. He's a
much better match for you.

480
00:29:34,830 --> 00:29:37,106
No, I insist. You take him.

481
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:39,816
No, you have him.

482
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:43,086
No, I'm letting you have
him. Driver Kim is all yours.

483
00:29:43,110 --> 00:29:45,456
Hae Ja.

484
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:47,586
- You take him.
- No, you take Driver Kim.

485
00:29:47,610 --> 00:29:50,810
It's you! You're a much
better match for him.

486
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:57,390
This substitute gig is no joke.

487
00:29:57,590 --> 00:29:59,060
Oh, my. This is tough.

488
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:01,430
I couldn't do all this even
if there were two of me.

489
00:30:02,530 --> 00:30:03,630
Oh, my gosh.

490
00:30:06,430 --> 00:30:09,300
Are you filling in for Ms.
Koh today, Ms. Choi?

491
00:30:09,970 --> 00:30:11,970
- Yes.
- That explains it.

492
00:30:12,370 --> 00:30:14,200
I had a dream last night.

493
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:17,240
You know, Ms. Choi.

494
00:30:20,010 --> 00:30:21,580
Looking at you up close,

495
00:30:22,010 --> 00:30:23,550
your eyes are so clear.

496
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:26,780
Like the ocean shimmering in the moonlight,

497
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,390
they just sparkle.

498
00:30:31,620 --> 00:30:33,036
Hae Ja, by any chance,

499
00:30:33,060 --> 00:30:35,230
have you ever heard of the word "yoonseul?"

500
00:30:37,060 --> 00:30:38,200
Spare me the poetry.

501
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:41,846
What's with the buttery voice?

502
00:30:41,870 --> 00:30:44,940
Let's get going. I'm crazy busy today.

503
00:30:49,910 --> 00:30:50,910
All clear.

504
00:30:52,180 --> 00:30:53,980
Right, we should go.

505
00:30:54,910 --> 00:30:56,180
Let's go.

506
00:31:12,930 --> 00:31:13,930
Get in.

507
00:31:17,870 --> 00:31:20,470
What's with the car? I
thought you only cycled.

508
00:31:20,670 --> 00:31:22,910
It's my mom's. She
was junking it, so I took it.

509
00:31:25,710 --> 00:31:28,080
By the way, how's your mom doing?

510
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,650
I've been meaning to go see her.

511
00:31:29,750 --> 00:31:32,350
It's fine. It's a six-bed ward,
so there's no room anyway.

512
00:31:33,380 --> 00:31:35,490
Are the hospital bills sorted out?

513
00:31:35,590 --> 00:31:37,826
Yes, I explained my situation
to the family I tutor for,

514
00:31:37,850 --> 00:31:39,766
and they gave me a
three-month advance on my pay.

515
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:40,890
That's a relief.

516
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,566
So, are you heading to the hospital now?

517
00:31:43,590 --> 00:31:47,030
No, I was at the hospital overnight,
so Yeong Rye is there today.

518
00:31:47,860 --> 00:31:49,600
I need to go home and see the kids.

519
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:52,200
Really?

520
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,586
- Get out.
- What?

521
00:32:02,610 --> 00:32:04,586
Take the bus. Something just came up.

522
00:32:04,610 --> 00:32:05,720
Hurry up and get out.

523
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:08,820
There you go.

524
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,260
Okay.

525
00:32:20,830 --> 00:32:23,130
What's with this guy? First
he says get in, then get out.

526
