796
00:52:41,220 --> 00:52:43,396
No, it's just that they're both nice.

797
00:52:43,420 --> 00:52:45,490
I'm fine with either one. Let's hurry.

798
00:52:46,290 --> 00:52:47,920
- Which one...
- Hey!

799
00:52:48,020 --> 00:52:49,090
Get down!

800
00:52:50,190 --> 00:52:51,290
What is it?

801
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:53,960
What?

802
00:52:55,160 --> 00:52:56,170
What?

803
00:53:03,570 --> 00:53:05,870
Why does the window display look so tacky?

804
00:53:06,840 --> 00:53:09,156
Don't you know that display is
everything in a department store?

805
00:53:09,180 --> 00:53:11,480
There's no highlight in this display!

806
00:53:11,580 --> 00:53:13,480
Is this what I pay you for?

807
00:53:13,550 --> 00:53:14,850
I'll fix it right away, sir.

808
00:53:15,980 --> 00:53:17,190
For goodness' sake.

809
00:53:39,680 --> 00:53:40,680
So...

810
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:44,680
The CEO of this
department store is your dad?

811
00:53:50,020 --> 00:53:51,720
And it's not even your birthday?

812
00:54:01,030 --> 00:54:02,436
If I'd known sooner,

813
00:54:02,460 --> 00:54:04,630
I would've been getting
a gift, not buying one.

814
00:54:10,440 --> 00:54:11,710
Well, one thing's for sure.

815
00:54:14,280 --> 00:54:16,580
Of everyone I know, you're...

816
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:22,890
You're the richest kid.

817
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:26,296
Gosh.

818
00:54:26,320 --> 00:54:27,390
Rich.

819
00:54:27,590 --> 00:54:28,760
Right. Okay.

820
00:54:29,060 --> 00:54:30,790
I guess I'm rich,

821
00:54:31,290 --> 00:54:34,930
but my father is the one
with the money, not me.

822
00:54:35,130 --> 00:54:36,830
But it'll all be yours eventually, right?

823
00:54:37,570 --> 00:54:38,570
So...

824
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:41,500
Why were you trying so desperately to hide?

825
00:54:42,140 --> 00:54:45,610
What if you ran into him? Would
he beat you up or something?

826
00:54:52,950 --> 00:54:56,650
So even a department
store CEO beats his own son.

827
00:54:59,820 --> 00:55:00,920
Well...

828
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:03,030
That's a new one.

829
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:09,476
He's always had a temper,

830
00:55:09,500 --> 00:55:12,000
but he wasn't always this violent.

831
00:55:13,540 --> 00:55:15,640
Not until my mom passed away.

832
00:55:17,140 --> 00:55:18,640
His self-control has been...

833
00:55:23,510 --> 00:55:25,756
You know...

834
00:55:25,780 --> 00:55:28,350
Your typical sob story.

835
00:55:30,850 --> 00:55:33,360
I mean, I'm used to it by now, so I'm fine.

836
00:55:34,690 --> 00:55:37,230
But when you were there with me,

837
00:55:38,630 --> 00:55:39,800
it was just a little...

838
00:55:50,740 --> 00:55:52,110
You're not okay either, though.

839
00:55:56,350 --> 00:55:57,910
You don't have to act so tough.

840
00:56:01,750 --> 00:56:04,550
If you always pretend you're
fine, you'll just fall apart all at once.

841
00:56:07,220 --> 00:56:08,990
It's better to admit when you're hurting.

842
00:56:10,730 --> 00:56:11,830
Yes.

843
00:56:17,570 --> 00:56:18,870
How do you know that so well?

844
00:56:19,670 --> 00:56:20,900
Because I've been there.

845
00:56:22,570 --> 00:56:24,910
Acted tough, and then just...

846
00:56:59,370 --> 00:57:00,380
Call me sometime.

847
00:57:02,710 --> 00:57:05,080
We could go to the library
this weekend or something.

848
00:57:08,620 --> 00:57:11,190
You already gave me your
number, and I shot you down.

849
00:57:11,390 --> 00:57:12,390
I know.

850
00:57:14,260 --> 00:57:15,820
Since I've already been shot down once,

851
00:57:16,630 --> 00:57:18,510
I figure a second time
will be less of a shock.

852
00:57:25,800 --> 00:57:26,800
I

853
00:57:37,080 --> 00:57:38,080
I

854
00:57:41,450 --> 00:57:42,750
I want to be with you.

855
00:58:07,110 --> 00:58:10,810
(Wonhwa Jaeil Hospital)

856
00:58:11,510 --> 00:58:13,350
- Here you go.
- Gosh. Thank you.

857
00:58:13,550 --> 00:58:16,220
- I hope that was enough.
- Not at all.

858
00:58:16,720 --> 00:58:18,166
- Thank you.
- You take care now.

859
00:58:18,190 --> 00:58:19,190
Okay.

860
00:59:04,670 --> 00:59:06,600
- Good grief.
- Oh, my gosh.

861
00:59:07,340 --> 00:59:10,060
Are your eyes just for decoration?
How could you possibly miss this?

862
00:59:11,110 --> 00:59:12,210
You startled me.

863
00:59:12,840 --> 00:59:14,086
You're still up?

864
00:59:14,110 --> 00:59:15,280
Here.

865
00:59:16,110 --> 00:59:18,080
Slather it on every time
you wash your hands.

866
00:59:19,380 --> 00:59:23,020
It's that hand cream all
the young people are using.

867
00:59:24,020 --> 00:59:25,090
Did you

868
00:59:25,290 --> 00:59:29,166
buy this for me, Mom?

869
00:59:29,190 --> 00:59:32,260
Of course I did. Did you
think it fell from the sky?

870
00:59:32,890 --> 00:59:35,100
Your youth is more precious than gold.

871
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:37,970
You need to start using this
thing while you're still young.

872
00:59:38,200 --> 00:59:41,240
Otherwise, your hands will end up
a wrinkly mess like your mother's.

873
00:59:43,140 --> 00:59:45,770
Gosh. What's gotten into
you, buying something like this?

874
00:59:51,710 --> 00:59:52,910
It smells nice.

875
00:59:53,380 --> 00:59:55,696
Goodness. Don't be stingy with it.

876
00:59:55,720 --> 00:59:57,766
- I'll buy you more when you're out.
- It feels like a waste, Mom.

877
00:59:57,790 --> 00:59:59,760
What's there to waste?
I said I'll buy you more.

878
01:00:01,390 --> 01:00:02,390
It feels so soft.

879
01:00:03,130 --> 01:00:04,390
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

880
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:07,976
Let's put some on you too, Mom.

881
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:09,576
- No, I'm okay.
- Come on, let me.

882
01:00:09,600 --> 01:00:10,800
I'm too old for this.

883
01:00:23,510 --> 01:00:24,610
Yeong Mi.

884
01:00:25,450 --> 01:00:26,427
Yes?

885
01:00:26,451 --> 01:00:28,650
Do you think my face looks any lighter?

886
01:00:30,650 --> 01:00:31,966
No, it's the same.

887
01:00:31,990 --> 01:00:32,990
Dark.

888
01:00:34,820 --> 01:00:35,996
- Yeong Bae.
- What?

889
01:00:36,020 --> 01:00:38,660
That omelette rice was so good, right?

890
01:00:39,460 --> 01:00:41,936
It was so yellow and fluffy.

891
01:00:41,960 --> 01:00:43,060
It really was.

892
01:00:43,270 --> 01:00:44,746
And there was meat inside, right?

893
01:00:44,770 --> 01:00:45,747
Yes, there was.

894
01:00:45,771 --> 01:00:47,276
Don't you want to have it again?

895
01:00:47,300 --> 01:00:48,370
I do.

896
01:00:50,140 --> 01:00:53,110
Sae Ri said we could come over again.

897
01:01:02,320 --> 01:01:05,550
Oh, my. What brings you two here?

898
01:01:05,650 --> 01:01:07,190
- Hello.
- Hello.

899
01:01:07,290 --> 01:01:09,596
Sae Ri invited us to come over again.

900
01:01:09,620 --> 01:01:10,730
I see.

901
01:01:11,290 --> 01:01:12,630
But what's this?

902
01:01:12,830 --> 01:01:15,006
Mom said when you visit someone's house,

903
01:01:15,030 --> 01:01:17,700
you shouldn't show up empty-handed.

904
01:01:18,030 --> 01:01:19,100
Okay.

905
01:01:19,300 --> 01:01:20,800
- This is for you.
- Okay.

906
01:01:21,240 --> 01:01:22,440
Oh, dear.

907
01:01:22,700 --> 01:01:25,340
All right. Take your
shoes off and come on in.

908
01:01:25,540 --> 01:01:27,016
Yeong Bae! Yeong Mi!

909
01:01:27,040 --> 01:01:28,140
Sae Ri!

910
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:30,010
Hi.

911
01:01:33,010 --> 01:01:34,980
It's the pumpkin from Cinderella!

912
01:01:35,580 --> 01:01:36,690
Yes, it is.

913
01:01:44,660 --> 01:01:46,576
You said you saw her, you punk.

914
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:48,406
When and where did you see her, you punk?

915
01:01:48,430 --> 01:01:50,430
I did see her at Yeonpung Intersection,

916
01:01:50,730 --> 01:01:52,400
but I was pretty wasted myself.

917
01:01:53,030 --> 01:01:54,646
So I didn't get the bus number.

918
01:01:54,670 --> 01:01:55,816
You punk.

919
01:01:55,840 --> 01:01:58,160
I wasn't sure at first because
of the conductor's uniform.

920
01:01:58,740 --> 01:02:01,980
But I'm sure of it. It
was definitely your sister.

921
01:02:05,180 --> 01:02:06,250
"A conductor's uniform?"

922
01:02:08,020 --> 01:02:09,720
That wench is working as a bus conductor?

923
01:02:51,660 --> 01:02:53,360
Like you could've gone far.

924
01:03:28,660 --> 01:03:31,430
- Yeong Rye!
- Hey!

925
01:03:31,800 --> 01:03:33,440
Hey!

926
01:03:36,470 --> 01:03:40,516
My goodness. It's been a
few days, but it feels like ages.

927
01:03:40,540 --> 01:03:42,816
I almost forgot what you look like.

928
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:44,010
Have you been well?

929
01:03:44,480 --> 01:03:46,250
I made things hard on all of you, didn't I?

930
01:03:47,180 --> 01:03:48,720
Hey, Koh Yeong Rye.

931
01:03:49,220 --> 01:03:50,450
It's been a while.

932
01:03:58,060 --> 01:03:59,160
Ta-da!

933
01:04:01,300 --> 01:04:02,500
Looks delicious.

934
01:04:04,570 --> 01:04:06,630
Let me get that for you. Hang on.

935
01:04:09,040 --> 01:04:10,370
Here, eat up.

936
01:04:15,240 --> 01:04:17,210
Anyone would think you're the patient.

937
01:04:17,980 --> 01:04:19,450
You've lost more weight.

938
01:04:21,050 --> 01:04:22,980
I've been trying to eat properly.

939
01:04:24,190 --> 01:04:25,966
Finish this and have some
more. I'll make another bowl.

940
01:04:25,990 --> 01:04:26,990
Okay.

941
01:04:29,820 --> 01:04:31,690
Here, for dessert.

942
01:04:32,260 --> 01:04:33,260
Thank you.

943
01:04:40,400 --> 01:04:42,170
I ran into Han Jae Pil yesterday.

944
01:04:45,210 --> 01:04:47,570
I guess he somehow found
out that Vivaldi is my usual spot.

945
01:04:48,710 --> 01:04:49,880
He was waiting for me.

946
01:04:52,980 --> 01:04:54,720
It was his birthday, so we ate.

947
01:04:54,820 --> 01:04:56,580
Then we went gift shopping.

948
01:04:57,390 --> 01:04:59,190
You know Dongin Department Store, right?

949
01:04:59,620 --> 01:05:00,990
It turns out his family owns it.

950
01:05:01,860 --> 01:05:03,660
He saw his dad and tried to hide from him.

951
01:05:04,590 --> 01:05:06,560
I think his father is kind of abusive.

952
01:05:06,760 --> 01:05:08,100
And his mother passed away.

953
01:05:09,760 --> 01:05:12,200
I guess money really can't buy happiness.

954
01:05:15,270 --> 01:05:16,270
Right.

955
01:05:16,810 --> 01:05:18,446
Then he gave me his number,

956
01:05:18,470 --> 01:05:20,790
and asked me to go to the
library with him on the weekend.

957
01:05:29,380 --> 01:05:30,390
And?

958
01:05:32,390 --> 01:05:33,520
What about you?

959
01:05:34,220 --> 01:05:35,220
What?

960
01:05:35,960 --> 01:05:37,130
Are you still

961
01:05:38,090 --> 01:05:39,760
not interested in him?

962
01:05:41,300 --> 01:05:42,300
Not at all?

963
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:44,500
I don't know.

964
01:05:47,440 --> 01:05:48,640
There's something about him.

965
01:05:50,770 --> 01:05:52,970
On one hand, it seems
like he has everything,

966
01:05:53,840 --> 01:05:55,580
but on the other, it's like he has nothing.

967
01:05:56,080 --> 01:05:57,410
He seems lonely.

968
01:06:00,620 --> 01:06:02,750
He does get on my mind, strangely enough.

969
01:06:09,260 --> 01:06:11,630
So why not give him a chance?

970
01:06:11,830 --> 01:06:13,760
A guy who asks me to the library on a date?

971
01:06:14,430 --> 01:06:16,000
No way. That's so lame.

972
01:06:24,670 --> 01:06:26,670
The fact that he doesn't
really know who I am,

973
01:06:27,940 --> 01:06:29,940
and the fact that I'm not
being honest with him.

974
01:06:31,280 --> 01:06:32,580
I don't like either one.

975
01:06:40,360 --> 01:06:41,660
Don't you think it's because

976
01:06:42,520 --> 01:06:44,590
you're starting to have feelings for him?

977
01:06:46,060 --> 01:06:48,500
Otherwise, you wouldn't
be so upset about it.

978
01:06:51,130 --> 01:06:52,300
Is that right?

979
01:06:58,970 --> 01:07:00,840
I don't even know how I feel.

980
01:07:03,710 --> 01:07:05,230
But there's one thing I know for sure.

981
01:07:06,480 --> 01:07:08,520
I think I have to see him one more time.

982
01:07:09,820 --> 01:07:11,950
I should probably start by being honest.

983
01:07:12,820 --> 01:07:15,320
That I'm not a student,
and I'm a bus conductor.

984
01:07:17,260 --> 01:07:19,560
And I'll just figure out the rest after that.

985
01:07:20,500 --> 01:07:23,360
I mean, we'll either see
each other or we won't, right?

986
01:07:27,770 --> 01:07:28,870
Oh, right.

987
01:07:29,570 --> 01:07:31,340
I have a full shift that day.

988
01:07:33,270 --> 01:07:35,140
So I didn't even have time anyway.

989
01:07:45,790 --> 01:07:48,220
I'll cover your shift.

990
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:54,230
You covered for me before.

991
01:07:54,960 --> 01:07:56,430
- Really?
- Yes.

992
01:07:58,300 --> 01:07:59,600
You'd really do that?

993
01:08:00,300 --> 01:08:01,300
Yes.

994
01:08:07,610 --> 01:08:08,610
Okay.

995
01:08:10,280 --> 01:08:11,280
All right, then.

996
01:08:13,380 --> 01:08:15,120
I'm going to go make the call.

997
01:08:15,320 --> 01:08:17,296
You finish this up, and just tidy up a little.

998
01:08:17,320 --> 01:08:18,320
Okay.

999
01:08:51,450 --> 01:08:53,320
Yes, hello?

1000
01:08:58,860 --> 01:09:00,030
Hello?

1001
01:09:06,430 --> 01:09:07,500
Hello?

1002
01:09:08,000 --> 01:09:09,940
If you're going to call,
at least say something.

1003
01:09:10,470 --> 01:09:11,570
Who is this?

1004
01:09:12,310 --> 01:09:13,516
Who are you, you punk?

1005
01:09:13,540 --> 01:09:16,180
This little brat. Who are
you, making a prank call?

1006
01:09:16,380 --> 01:09:17,680
Who are you, you punk?

1007
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:21,120
Unbelievable.

1008
01:09:23,450 --> 01:09:26,366
Anyway, people like this should
all be rounded up and jailed.

1009
01:09:26,390 --> 01:09:27,420
These little punks.

1010
01:09:28,520 --> 01:09:30,320
The laws in this country
are way too lenient.

1011
01:09:48,080 --> 01:09:49,180
Hello?

1012
01:09:49,380 --> 01:09:50,380
Hey.

1013
01:09:51,510 --> 01:09:52,880
It's me, Seo Jong Hee.

1014
01:09:54,250 --> 01:09:55,250
Hey.

1015
01:09:56,020 --> 01:09:57,020
What?

1016
01:09:57,320 --> 01:09:59,920
I'm at a payphone, and
I'm down to my last dime.

1017
01:10:00,220 --> 01:10:01,990
I'll make this quick, so listen up.

1018
01:10:03,320 --> 01:10:04,330
Okay.

1019
01:10:04,430 --> 01:10:06,290
Meet me in front of
Vivaldi on Sunday at 1pm.

1020
01:10:06,890 --> 01:10:09,010
There's something I need
to tell you in person first.

1021
01:10:11,430 --> 01:10:13,970
No, it's not something I
can say over the phone.

1022
01:10:16,340 --> 01:10:17,340
Right.

1023
01:10:18,340 --> 01:10:21,010
It was bound to end up like this anyway.

1024
01:10:23,140 --> 01:10:24,940
More than my three
fated encounters with him,

1025
01:10:25,210 --> 01:10:30,120
their one encounter was a
stronger and more powerful destiny.

1026
01:10:34,260 --> 01:10:35,320
So.

1027
01:10:36,090 --> 01:10:39,660
I'm taking back my claim to happiness.

1028
01:10:40,630 --> 01:10:41,660
Because...

1029
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:53,880
You also have the right to
pursue your own happiness.

1030
01:10:55,310 --> 01:10:56,380
And...

1031
01:10:57,450 --> 01:11:01,550
The person I want to be
happy, second only to myself,

1032
01:11:05,550 --> 01:11:07,860
is you.

1033
01:11:31,580 --> 01:11:32,580
Yes.

1034
01:11:47,200 --> 01:11:48,360
That's nice.

1035
01:11:48,760 --> 01:11:50,236
But why the pumpkin
porridge all of a sudden?

1036
01:11:50,260 --> 01:11:52,606
The tutor's younger
siblings brought it over.

1037
01:11:52,630 --> 01:11:53,800
- His siblings?
- Yes.

1038
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:56,716
His little brother is around Sae Ri's age,

1039
01:11:56,740 --> 01:11:58,970
and his sister is a
couple of years younger.

1040
01:11:59,170 --> 01:12:01,386
I guess the tutor is the eldest son.

1041
01:12:01,410 --> 01:12:03,186
Their father passed away young...

1042
01:12:03,210 --> 01:12:05,086
There's no need to be,

1043
01:12:05,110 --> 01:12:07,620
so nosy about other
people's family business.

1044
01:12:08,650 --> 01:12:09,726
He's not a stranger.

1045
01:12:09,750 --> 01:12:11,026
- Sae Ri, come on.
- Yes, Sae Ri.

1046
01:12:11,050 --> 01:12:12,250
- Have a seat.
- Come sit here.

1047
01:12:13,790 --> 01:12:14,966
- Eat your porridge.
- That's a good girl.

1048
01:12:14,990 --> 01:12:16,136
- It's hot, so make sure...
- Eat up.

1049
01:12:16,160 --> 01:12:17,137
You blow on it before you eat.

1050
01:12:17,161 --> 01:12:18,360
- Okay.
- Okay.

1051
01:12:24,630 --> 01:12:25,630
Is it good?

1052
01:12:26,570 --> 01:12:28,170
- Mom.
- Yes?

1053
01:12:28,700 --> 01:12:30,570
Where's my Cinderella pumpkin?

1054
01:12:31,170 --> 01:12:33,640
I put it over there, but it's gone now.

1055
01:12:34,380 --> 01:12:35,810
I wanted to keep it in my room.

1056
01:12:35,910 --> 01:12:36,916
That one?

1057
01:12:36,940 --> 01:12:38,850
Mommy made it into porridge.

1058
01:12:39,510 --> 01:12:41,180
You just ate it, Sae Ri.

1059
01:12:44,050 --> 01:12:45,750
- Can I have another bowl?
- Sure.

1060
01:12:51,460 --> 01:12:53,066
My Cinderella pumpkin!

1061
01:12:53,090 --> 01:12:55,006
- Why did you eat it?
- I'm leaving now.

1062
01:12:55,030 --> 01:12:56,676
I was supposed to make a carriage!

1063
01:12:56,700 --> 01:12:58,346
- Have some porridge before you go.
- I hate you, Mom!

1064
01:12:58,370 --> 01:13:00,170
It's Saturday, so you have no lunchbox.

1065
01:13:00,430 --> 01:13:01,676
No, I'm fine.

1066
01:13:01,700 --> 01:13:04,040
- I'm leaving now.
- My Cinderella pumpkin!

1067
01:13:10,410 --> 01:13:11,890
Are you back from your route already?

1068
01:13:12,080 --> 01:13:13,380
You're quick today.

1069
01:13:13,580 --> 01:13:16,980
Yes, it was pretty quiet out
there because it's Saturday.

1070
01:13:24,890 --> 01:13:25,890
Why?

1071
01:13:26,390 --> 01:13:27,400
Just because.

1072
01:13:28,030 --> 01:13:29,060
You're so pretty.

1073
01:13:30,460 --> 01:13:31,470
Of course.

1074
01:13:31,670 --> 01:13:33,800
I'm one of the prettiest
faces here at Cheongah Bus.

1075
01:13:36,200 --> 01:13:37,540
You really are.

1076
01:13:38,270 --> 01:13:39,540
Even now.

1077
01:13:44,380 --> 01:13:45,850
Right.

1078
01:13:46,710 --> 01:13:49,350
You're going to tell him tomorrow, right?

1079
01:13:50,050 --> 01:13:51,090
I have to.

1080
01:13:52,890 --> 01:13:54,590
- I'm off then.
- Okay.

1081
01:14:04,470 --> 01:14:07,230
Jong Hee!

1082
01:14:07,340 --> 01:14:10,370
Seo Jong Hee! You forgot your hat.

1083
01:14:10,570 --> 01:14:11,670
Darn it.

1084
01:14:11,770 --> 01:14:13,646
I mean, if there's a spot check from HQ,

1085
01:14:13,670 --> 01:14:16,040
she'll get in trouble for
a dress code violation.

1086
01:14:16,780 --> 01:14:17,780
Here, let me.

1087
01:14:17,980 --> 01:14:19,626
- I'll run it over to her.
- What?

1088
01:14:19,650 --> 01:14:22,820
The bus has already left.
How can you possibly catch it?

1089
01:14:54,050 --> 01:14:56,180
Are you okay? You're not hurt, are you?

1090
01:14:56,550 --> 01:14:58,490
Oh, my gosh. I'm so sorry.

1091
01:14:59,490 --> 01:15:01,460
The tire suddenly went flat.

1092
01:15:01,990 --> 01:15:04,830
I'm afraid you all need to
get off and take the next bus.

1093
01:15:05,030 --> 01:15:06,860
- Gosh.
- I'm sorry.

1094
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:10,060
- Please get off.
- I'm sorry.

1095
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:11,776
Everyone, please exit. I'm sorry.

1096
01:15:11,800 --> 01:15:12,800
Oh, come one.

1097
01:15:13,730 --> 01:15:14,970
That was a close call.

1098
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:16,370
I'm sorry.

1099
01:15:17,540 --> 01:15:18,710
I'm sorry.

1100
01:15:20,370 --> 01:15:21,510
I'm sorry.

1101
01:15:23,140 --> 01:15:24,180
I'm sorry.

1102
01:15:44,400 --> 01:15:46,870
If I'm late, I'm on cleaning duty again.

1103
01:15:47,940 --> 01:15:50,000
I'll take the next bus, and...

1104
01:15:51,370 --> 01:15:53,040
Would it be faster if I can transfer?

1105
01:17:36,080 --> 01:17:38,710
(A Hundred Memories)

1106
01:17:57,060 --> 01:17:59,876
Weren't you planning on telling him anyway?

1107
01:17:59,900 --> 01:18:00,877
I know.

1108
01:18:00,901 --> 01:18:04,076
But letting him know myself
and getting caught is different.

1109
01:18:04,100 --> 01:18:05,246
It doesn't matter to me.

1110
01:18:05,270 --> 01:18:06,416
It does for me.

1111
01:18:06,440 --> 01:18:07,720
Don't come looking for me again.

1112
01:18:07,910 --> 01:18:09,140
Let me ask you one thing.

1113
01:18:09,240 --> 01:18:11,426
Is there a bus conductor
named Seo Jong Yeon here?

1114
01:18:11,450 --> 01:18:15,326
A strange man came looking for
someone called Seo Jong Yeon.

1115
01:18:15,350 --> 01:18:16,626
What's going on, Jong Hee?

1116
01:18:16,650 --> 01:18:17,990
- We can't stop.
- Stop!

1117
01:18:18,290 --> 01:18:19,526
We have to go faster.

1118
01:18:19,550 --> 01:18:21,790
- Stop!
- Please, leave me alone.

1119
01:18:21,890 --> 01:18:24,930
I'm already embarrassed
as is, that everyone knows.

1120
01:18:25,030 --> 01:18:26,106
Let go!

1121
01:18:26,130 --> 01:18:28,130
Let me stay by your
side, even just as a friend.
